        <abstract> 
<p>Mentions Dutch translation [of <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>].</p> 
            <p>Discusses evolutionary origin of sexuality.</p>
            <p>Asa Gray’s suggestion that variation was directed by a higher power and Herschel’s view of providential arrangement in nature.</p>
            <p>Compares variation in domestic and wild species.</p>
            <p>Asks CL for introductions for his son William in Southampton, where he has joined a bank.</p>
        </abstract>
